To test the performance of the pipeline on individual categories and to assess their contributions to the overall results, we ran extTADA separately on each of four single variant classes: silentFCPk, MiD, and LoF DN mutations, and MiD+LoF CC variants (Additional file 1: Table S9). All parameter estimates were consistent with the primary analysis, with broader CIs. The much larger \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
